cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD

This paper is about the effects of visual stimulus deficits on the training of artificial neural networks (ANNs), which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on deep neural networks (DNNs), which are a subset of ANNs commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses techniques from information theory to study the strength of network connections during training, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
